# Token Economics (R1-Q7)

## North Star

**Performance Per Token** — quality improvement per dollar of API spend.

## Attribution Tagging

Every API call must be tagged with its purpose:

| Tag | Stage | Typical Tokens |
|-----|-------|---------------|
| `brief-expansion` | generate | ~300 |
| `generation` | generate | ~850 |
| `evaluation` | evaluate | ~1,240 |
| `regeneration-attempt-1` | iterate | ~1,100 |
| `regeneration-attempt-2` | iterate | ~1,100 |
| `regeneration-attempt-3` | iterate | ~1,100 |
| `context-distillation` | iterate | ~200 |
| `triage` | evaluate | ~500 |
| `compliance` | generate | ~400 |

- `iterate/token_tracker.py` owns attribution (P1-11)
- Tags stored in `action` field of every ledger event
- `tokens_consumed` field on every event — never zero for API calls

## Three Metrics

| Metric | Formula | Use |
|--------|---------|-----|
| Cost per publishable ad | total tokens / published ads | Dashboard metric |
| QWTE | avg quality of published / tokens per published | Cross-batch comparison |
| Marginal analysis | quality delta / token delta per regen cycle | Optimization engine |

## Token Budget Projection (50 ads)

```
First pass (all 50): ~119,500 tokens (Flash)
Regen cycle 1 (15 ads × 5 variants): ~175,500 tokens (Pro)
Regen cycle 2 (5 ads × 5 variants): ~58,500 tokens (Pro)
Brief mutation + cycle 3 (2 ads): ~23,400 tokens (Pro)
Overhead: ~15,000 tokens (Flash)
TOTAL: ~392,000 tokens
Published: ~47 ads (94% success rate)
Cost per publishable ad: ~8,340 tokens
```

## Marginal Analysis

Track quality gain per regen cycle:
- If improvement between cycle N and N-1 < 0.3 points → diminishing returns
- Cycle 3 on Brand Voice issues: usually worth it (high marginal gain)
- Cycle 3 on Clarity issues: usually not worth it (diminishing returns)
- This data feeds back into dynamic regen budget decisions

## Do NOT

- Make API calls without `tokens_consumed` and `action` in the ledger event
- Ignore marginal analysis — it's what makes the system self-tuning
- Treat all regen cycles as equally valuable — later cycles have diminishing ROI
- Skip token counting on compliance or distillation calls — every token counts
